==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|envie}}, from {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|envie}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|invidia||envy}}, from {{m|la|invidere||to look at with malice}} from ''in'' + ''videre'' ("on, upon" + "to look, see"). Displaced native {{cog|enm|ande|ande, onde|envy}} (from {{cog|ang|anda|anda, onda|breath, emotion, envy, hatred, grudge, dislike}}), {{cog|enm|nith|nithe, nith|envy, malice}} (from {{cog|ang|nīþ||envy, hatred, malice, spite, jealousy}}).

